			<ns0:name>ncb...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/100032148147647801554/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Just to make sure it's documented, we've discovered this issue arises because NaCl is requesting a file descriptor for a file in the cache.  The cache code plays it safe by copying the file into a temp directory before opening it and handing the file descriptor to NaCl.

There are some deeper issues that need to be dealt with, beyond this bug.  For example, when we get to the point of mmaping nexes, this "copy on open" behavior will eliminate any memory sharing that would otherwise be possible.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-11-29T23:50:53.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-11-29T23:50:53.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 7 by ncb...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1981#c7" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1981/comments/full/7" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>